dismissalComment.html: bowled him, a slow legcutter! That's a corker of a delivery from Dernbach and it's his variations that have done for Elgar! dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Bopara c †de Villiers b Morkel 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: edged, he's given! Bopara reviews it. There was a sound. He reviewed straight away. No asking. Well, no mark on Hot Spot. There is certainly a sound. This will be interesting. Is there conclusive evidence to overrule? It stays out, Bopara isn't happy but under the DRS that is the correct decision. The third umpire, Taufel, said there was a clear sound and wasn't enough evidence to overrule.

headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: it's all over...drives a full ball over cover, not quite out of the middle but it gets the single they needed

commentPostTextItems.html: Presentation time...first it's AB de Villiers: "Thought it was a good toss to win, it wasn't a 210 wicket. The top order didn't take responsibility and we came up short. Most of our senior players got in and didn't make it count, including me, I played a very poor shot."

Alastair Cook: "A lot of character was shown there. It was a really good bowling performance. You wouldn't want to chase too many more on that wicket. Eoin and Jonathan played two very good innings. It's always nice to get a first win. There were a few nerves up there. Credit to the way we batted. So to cross the line is really pleasing. Jade came in, we wanted a wicket-taker, and he took wickets for us."

The Man of the Match goes to Eoin Morgan. Fair decision. He was the only batsman to score freely on the pitch. "Tonight the pitch played consistently throughout and I could play myself in. I've been in the side for a while now and I enjoy taking the reins in the middle order."

That wraps things up for the evening. It's all square with two to play and the next match is at Lord's on Sunday. There's still cricket going on today (or tomorrow, or whenever it is) with the ODI in Abu Dhabi. So you can head over there if you like. For now, though, from Andrew McGlashan and Alan Gardner it's goodbye and thanks for joining us.

England win by four wickets and the series is level. They are also back to No. 1 in the one-day rankings. A solid performance from the home side, sparked by the bowling of Jade Dernbach who was excellent on his recall. He was backed up by Ravi Bopara and James Anderson, while James Tredwell also took two important wickets on his return to the team. With the bat, England knew all they had to do was bat out the overs and they'd win. Eoin Morgan gave the innings important impetus while Jonathan Trott played the ideal anchor knock. We'll bring you news of the Man of the Match shortly. I'd go for Dernbach, personally, as I thought he made the different with key wickets. But it could also be either Trott or Morgan.

commentTextItems.html: flicked away off leg stump down to long leg so the scores are level
speared in full at leg stump, dug out to the leg side
played off the back foot and gets a controlled outside edge to third man
drives again and this time comes off a thick inner part of the bat to midwicket
driven on the up, was wide outside off and it went in the air for a while past a diving cover but well out of reach of the fielder
outside off and left alone...scoots fairly close to off stump. That ends an excellent 10 overs from Parnell.

commentPostTextItems.html: That ends a very solid, efficient, innings from Trott. Just what England needed this evening on a tricky surface for scoring. Home side need five more.

commentTextItems.html: drives and gets a thick edge into his pads which runs into the off side
very full, forced square of the wicket to point
short ball, goes for the pull and takes the top of the pad through to de Villiers
full outside off, driven with a bit of sparkle by Patel but straight to mid-off...been a lot of hitting fielders today
full outside off, pushed square into the off side where backward point parries it

commentTextItems.html: there's some aggression, picks up a length ball over mid-on and it goes two bounces to the boundary...strong shot
nicely bowled, full on off stump, hint of movement into Patel who defends
very full on middle, Trott plays across the line and works it wide of mid-on
wide outside off, Trott goes for a cut and doesn't connect...costs an extra ball and run, de Villiers not entirely impressed
he's creamed that, gave himself room outside leg and drilled his drive but straight to cover
bit of a flourish from Trott as he comes across the crease and whips this from outside off through midwicket...a mini flamingo maybe?
a full delivery on the stumps is nicely timed with a flick to mid-on...this is not ending in a flourish

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Smith b Anderson 18 (25b 2x4 0x6 37m) SR: 72

dismissalComment.html: advances and gone, bowled! Looks like Anderson rolled his fingers over the ball, again Smith's impatience got the better of him and he missed tried to pull through the on side, the ball flipping the leg bail off on its way through

headshotImage.caption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Hashim Amla b Dernbach 43 (51b 5x4 0x6 68m) SR: 84.31

dismissalComment.html: gone! He's got Amla. Something that England have found hard to do this summer. Was a full delivery which nipped back into Amla as he went for a drive and it takes an inside edge into leg stump

dismissalText.commentary: AB de Villiers c Bell b Tredwell 28 (31b 3x4 0x6 34m) SR: 90.32

dismissalComment.html: gone! Trying to repeat the flicks over midwicket he played in the last over but this time gets the shot too straight down the ground which allows Ian Bell to steady himself under the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Faf du Plessis b Bopara 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: gone! Du Plessis went too far across his stumps and loses his leg stump. He went down the pitch and outside off, the ball was angling towards the leg side and du Plessis missed his flick.

headshotImage.caption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dean Elgar b Dernbach 42 (61b 2x4 0x6 88m) SR: 68.85

dismissalComment.html: bowled him, a slow legcutter! That's a corker of a delivery from Dernbach and it's his variations that have done for Elgar! The ball came out the back of the hand, pitched on a length and came back in to hit the top of off as Elgar played around it, foxed by the lack of pace and now back in the chicken coop himself

headshotImage.caption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jade Dernbach player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Wayne Parnell c †Kieswetter b Dernbach 13 (8b 3x4 0x6 6m) SR: 162.5

dismissalComment.html: got him this time, edged to the keeper! Three in three for Dernbach to Parnell, the edges got progressively thinner and this one ended up comfortably in Kieswetter's bread basket. Parnell fails to make the most of his lives and England have taken the box seat in this game

dismissalText.commentary: Jean-Paul Duminy c Bell b Tredwell 33 (46b 2x4 0x6 61m) SR: 71.73

dismissalComment.html: strikes this time, though. Big wicket. Duminy comes down the pitch and tries to clear the straight boundary but gets it higher rather than longer and Ian Bell settles under his second catch, this time at long-off, although it didn't go in cleanly

dismissalText.commentary: Dale Steyn b Anderson 1 (7b 0x4 0x6 12m) SR: 14.28

dismissalComment.html: another one goes...a good delivery from Anderson. Full on off stump, the ball holds its line, and Steyn played all around it. Jimmy will have enjoyed that.

dismissalText.commentary: Morne Morkel b Anderson 7 (11b 1x4 0x6 8m) SR: 63.63

dismissalComment.html: cleaned up! Another for Anderson. Came into Morkel from round the wicket and scooted between bat and pad to take middle and off stump

headshotImage.longCaption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lonwabo Tsotsobe lbw b Anderson 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: given lbw! Tsotsobe uses the review that's left. May as well. Was trapped on the back foot. Maybe going over? He's not hit it. Just clipping the top of leg stump so that will stay on the field.

headshotImage.longCaption: Dean Elgar player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alastair Cook c Elgar b Peterson 20 (47b 3x4 0x6 68m) SR: 42.55

dismissalComment.html: gone! That's what pressure does. Another short ball from Peterson and Cooks it straight down the throat of deep midwicket. Pretty ordinary from the England captain. South Africa rewarded for tight overs

dismissalText.commentary: Ian Bell lbw b Steyn 12 (7b 3x4 0x6 8m) SR: 171.42

dismissalComment.html: full and straight and gone! Steyn is bang on to Bell and a review won't save him ... He was hit low on the pad, trying to play across the line and it's a good job he didn't resort to DRS because that was hitting middle and leg

headshotImage.caption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Jonathan Trott player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jonathan Trott c †de Villiers b Parnell 71 (125b 2x4 0x6 200m) SR: 56.8

dismissalComment.html: he won't see England home. Feels for a ball outside off going across him and gets a thin edge to de Villiers.

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Bopara c †de Villiers b Morkel 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: edged, he's given! Bopara reviews it. There was a sound. He reviewed straight away. No asking. Well, no mark on Hot Spot. There is certainly a sound. This will be interesting. Is there conclusive evidence to overrule? It stays out, Bopara isn't happy but under the DRS that is the correct decision. The third umpire, Taufel, said there was a clear sound and wasn't enough evidence to overrule.

headshotImage.longCaption: Robin Peterson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan c & b Peterson 73 (67b 7x4 2x6 89m) SR: 108.95

dismissalComment.html: slog-sweeps across the line and skied high into the air, Peterson steadies himself underneath it to complete the catch! Though he then let the ball slip out of his hand as he went to throw it back into the air in celebration, causing Morgan to linger ... but after a brief consultation between the umpires, he is rightly told to be on his way

headshotImage.caption: Robin Peterson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Robin Peterson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Kieswetter run out (Parnell/†de Villiers) 14 (18b 0x4 1x6 16m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: that's some poor cricket from England...Trott worked a full ball to mid-on and the throw to de Villiers is good enough to catch Kieswetter well short despite a dive
